---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	lang="en"
	title="Mountain destinations — Gandía 2026"
	description="Inland destinations behind the Costa Blanca — Aitana, Bèrnia, Mariola, road cycling and mountain trails, whitewashed villages and quiet sierras."
	otherLangHref="/es/montana/"
	otherLangLabel="Español"
>
	<p class="eyebrow">Mountain destinations</p>
	<h1>Into <span class="accent">the mountains</span></h1>
	<p class="tagline">
		The quiet sierras behind the Costa Blanca — rock-perched villages, cooler
		evenings, real stars overhead.
	</p>

	<figure class="hero">
		<img src="/images/mountain-02.jpg" alt="A view from a mountain pass over a green valley to a peaked sierra in the middle distance, with the Mediterranean coast visible in the far background under a cloudy sky." />
	</figure>

	<p>
		The Costa Blanca's inland is a stack of limestone sierras —
		<strong>Aitana, Bèrnia, Serrella, Mariola, Montgó</strong> — rising sharp
		behind the coast and falling away in long terraced valleys. Roads
		switchback up to whitewashed villages where life still slows to the
		rhythm of bread and the almond harvest. Stone is everywhere: in the
		houses, in the dry-stone walls climbing the hillsides, in the peaks
		themselves. And in places — Montgó, Bèrnia, the Cumbre del Sol —
		<strong>the mountains drop straight into the sea</strong>, carving out
		the cliff towns, the headlands and the hidden calas that make this coast
		unrepeatable. From the high passes, on a clear day, you can see the
		whole length of it.
	</p>

	<div class="gallery gallery-3">
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/mountain-01.jpg" alt="A whitewashed village with a church tower clustered at the foot of a tall grey limestone ridge, terraced fields and orchards below." />
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/mountain-06.jpg" alt="A young person sitting on a stone outcrop at a summit, looking out over forested ridges and valleys receding into a hazy distance." />
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/mountain-07.jpg" alt="A turquoise bay curving toward a coastal town at dusk, a red rocky headland in the foreground, mountains silhouetted on the horizon." />
		</figure>
	</div>

	<p>
		For <strong>road cyclists</strong>, this is one of Europe's best winters
		of riding — long warm climbs over Coll de Rates, Puerto de Tudons and
		the back roads to Famorca and Confrides, empty asphalt and half-hour
		descents. <strong>Mountain biking</strong> takes to the limestone tracks
		above Dénia and Pego. <strong>Walkers</strong> have endless marked GR
		and PR trails between the villages, summit paths that reward the climb
		with the whole coast at your feet, and the <strong>trail-running</strong>
		calendar puts on a race somewhere in the sierras most weekends in
		spring and autumn.
	</p>

	<div class="gallery">
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/mountain-03.jpg" alt="An aerial view of a marina packed with white yachts, a coastal town and hazy mountain ridges receding into the distance." />
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/mountain-04.jpg" alt="A high panorama over the bay of Calpe — the Peñón de Ifach rock on the left, a rounded headland on the right, the city spread between them, the Mediterranean glittering below." />
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/mountain-05.jpg" alt="A wide blue sea horizon seen from a clifftop high above the coast — towns clinging to the cliffs left and right, sparse green shrub in the foreground." />
		</figure>
		<figure>
			<img src="/images/mountain-08.jpg" alt="A walker on a rocky summit reading an interpretation panel — a vast cloudscape above, sierras receding to the horizon and a coastal town spread out far below." />
		</figure>
	</div>

	<p>
		And then the villages themselves — <strong>Bocairent</strong>,
		<strong>Guadalest</strong>, <strong>Vall de Gallinera</strong>,
		<strong>Tàrbena</strong>, <strong>Castell de Castells</strong>. Small,
		kept, lived-in. Tiny family restaurants where the cook is the owner and
		the day's menu fits on a chalkboard: <strong>olleta</strong> with
		mountain beans, <strong>arròs caldós</strong> with rabbit and rosemary,
		<strong>embotits</strong> cured in the village, almond cake, the sweet
		wines of Xaló. Real food, made the way it's always been made.
		<strong>Tell us what you want to ride, walk or eat</strong> — we'll plan
		the route, the picnic, the table, the bed.
	</p>

	<style>
		.gallery {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
			gap: 0.9rem;
			margin: 2.6rem 0;
		}
		.gallery-3 { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
		.gallery figure { margin: 0; }
		.gallery img {
			width: 100%;
			height: 100%;
			aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
			object-fit: cover;
			border-radius: 6px;
			box-shadow: 0 4px 18px rgba(31, 27, 22, 0.10);
			display: block;
		}
		@media (max-width: 640px) {
			.gallery { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
		}
	</style>
</Layout>
